%N A392920 Number of gapless Gog triangles of size n such that the corresponding alternating sign matrix is symmetric.
%C A392920 A Gog triangle of size n is a Gelfand-Tsetlin pattern (X_{i,j})_{1<=j<=i<=n} with bottom row 1 2 3 ... n and strictly increasing rows.
%C A392920 A Gelfand-Tsetlin pattern is said to be gapless if X_{i+1,j+1} - X_{i,j} is at most 1.
%C A392920 Gog triangles are in bijection with alternating sign matrices (ASM) through the following bijection: A Gog triangle X is mapped to the ASM M such that M_{i,j} = 1 if row i of X contains the value j and this value is not in the previous row; M_{i,j} = -1 if row i of X does not contain the value j and this value is in the previous row.
%C A392920 The set of ASMs corresponding to gapless Gog triangles is invariant by transposition.
%H A392920 Ludovic Schwob, <a href="/A392920/b392920.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..31</a>
%H A392920 Ludovic Schwob, <a href="/A392920/a392920.txt">Python program</a>
%e A392920 The 6 gapless Gog triangles of size 3 and the corresponding ASMs are:
%e A392920     1           2           2           3           2           3
%e A392920    1 2         1 2         1 3         2 3         2 3         1 3
%e A392920   1 2 3       1 2 3       1 2 3       1 2 3       1 2 3       1 2 3
%e A392920 .
%e A392920  [1    ]     [  1  ]     [   1  ]    [    1]     [  1  ]     [    1]
%e A392920  [  1  ]     [1    ]     [1 -1 1]    [  1  ]     [    1]     [1    ]
%e A392920  [    1]     [    1]     [   1  ]    [1    ]     [1    ]     [  1  ]
%e A392920 Only the first four ASMs are symmetric, giving a(3) = 4.
